<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Flipcart</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <div class="company-info">
            <h2 >About Flipcart</h2>
            <p>
                <strong>Flipkart</strong> is one of India’s leading e-commerce companies, revolutionizing online shopping in the country. Founded in <strong>2007 by Sachin Bansal and Binny Bansal</strong>, Flipkart began as an online bookstore. The two founders, former Amazon employees, envisioned Flipkart as a platform to cater to the growing demand for online shopping in India, where access to physical stores was limited in many regions.
                <br><br>

                Initially, Flipkart started by selling books, but the founders quickly expanded their product range to include electronics, home appliances, clothing, and a variety of other consumer goods. The company’s unique selling point was its focus on providing a convenient and customer-friendly shopping experience, backed by services like easy returns, fast delivery, and customer support.
                <br><br>
                
                In 2010, Flipkart expanded its product offerings further and launched several innovative features, including Cash on Delivery (COD), which played a significant role in building trust among Indian customers, many of whom were hesitant about online payments. Over the years, Flipkart continued to grow, attracting investment from global giants, including Tiger Global, Accel Partners, and Microsoft. This led to its acquisition by Walmart in 2018 for $16 billion, marking one of the largest acquisitions in the Indian e-commerce space.
                <br><br>
                
                The company has also made several strategic acquisitions, such as Myntra (a major online fashion retailer) and Jabong, further expanding its footprint in the e-commerce sector.
                <br><br>
                
                As of 2024, the CEO of Flipkart is <strong>Kalyan Krishnamurthy</strong>, who took over the role in 2017. Krishnamurthy, an experienced leader in the tech and e-commerce industries, has played a pivotal role in scaling Flipkart’s operations, ensuring its competitiveness against other e-commerce giants like Amazon India and Snapdeal.
                <br><br>
                
                Flipkart continues to be a dominant force in the Indian market, providing a wide range of products, from electronics to groceries, and increasingly focusing on digital services, such as fintech and cloud computing. Its continued success and expansion are driven by its strong leadership, innovative offerings, and ability to cater to the evolving demands of the Indian consumer market.
                
                
                  
          
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </main>

